      {
        "position": 3,
        "title": "Absolutely amazing fabric",
        "text": "This material is so cool, and this little vest solves so many problems that I've had with other types of doggie clothes. I have a miniature dachshund and she gets nervous for some reason when I put any type of harness/vest/jacket/sweater on her. She doesn't like anything being stretched over her head, and she doesn't like when I grab her paws and try to direct them through a hole. She also really does not like the sound of velcro ripping apart like when I take off her walking harness, so the silently detaching fabric is really fantastic. Another huge problem is that her legs are so short, if she's wearing something with any kind of sleeves, her front legs usually end up getting stuck inside and then she can't walk at all. She has needed surgery for a couple of ruptured disks years ago, so I like to use a harness when I take her for walks, but it's just always a challenge to put it on or take it off without her leaking a little pee during the process of putting it on. I do like how this vest is very adjustable and versatile being in 2 pieces, but there were just a couple of reasons that I didn't think it was a perfect 5-star product. I thought the price was on the high side at first, but after I investigated this fabric, it's very expensive from the source so I'm not too surprised. Also the shape is a little strange for my dog's body and it hangs a little weird, like around her neck. I know it's supposed to be a calming vest, but it has the opposite effect on my dog, and she's really only nervous when she's wearing something. She's not at all afraid of fireworks or thunder, so I mainly wanted to use this for warmth in the winter months. I know it's not advertised for that purpose, and I was just hoping it would be a little thicker. It's really nice and innovative, but I just don't think I'll be getting as much use out of this as I had imagined. It's really a cool product, and thank you so much for letting me try it out.",
        "rating": 4,
